        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-18T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-18T22:00:00-05:00" n="297"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/5282: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-19T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 19, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 19—6:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>465. Legation’s 462, June 18, 3 p.m.<note n="55" xml:id="d297fn55">Not
                        printed.</note> Following from Reuters, Shanghai, June 17th: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“T. V. Soong, Minister of Finance, has made the following statement:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>‘The forcible seizure of the Tientsin custom[s] by agents of the
                                    militarists constitutes a serious blow to the national credit,
                                    endangering <pb facs="0338" n="240" xml:id="pg_240"/> all future
                                    plans for financial rehabilitation as well as existing foreign
                                    and domestic obligations secured on the customs.</p>
                                <p>Colonel Hayley Bell has maintained the best traditions of the
                                    service in refusing to allow the disruption of the integrity of
                                    the customs. Steps are however being taken which will insure the
                                    collapse of this phase of the militarists’ adventure very
                                    shortly.</p>
                                <p>This desperate act of the Northern faction in trying to destroy
                                    the only possible instrument of the national credit is a
                                    sufficient refutation of their own claim that they would very
                                    shortly be able to overthrow the National Government and
                                    establish a government of their own.’”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
